        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>A hand-colored, illustrated map of part of the town of Flatbush in Brooklyn, made by Teunis G. Bergen while he attended school in Flatbush (presumably at Erasmus Hall Academy).</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <bioghist id="ref5">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Teunis G. Bergen (1806-1881) was a Brooklyn surveyor and historian who served as New Utrecht town supervisor from 1836 to 1859 and as a Democratic congressman from the Second District.</p>
        </bioghist>
